Slope (average)



Sometimes, it can be useful to find the average rate of change of a function. Between any two points on a function \((x_1,y_1)\) and \((x_2,y_2)\) the slope is found by:}

\[m=\frac{\Delta y}{\Delta x}=\frac{y_2-y_1}{x_2-x_1}\]
